# Hand-labeled entity gold for cross-source entity-linking precision/recall (Phase 6.2).
# One row per entity node the linker ADMITTED (all 29). `is_bridge` = a genuine
# real-world entity whose doc mention meaningfully bridges to the DB column it links to.
# Rationale grounded in the actual doc corpus:
#   generic_readme.txt is an EXPLICIT negative ("contains no property, asset, or
#   financial records and should not link to any structured source") — anything from it
#   is a false positive by design.  site_notes.md / maintenance_policy.docx /
#   msa_green_tower.pdf carry the genuine amenity / city / financial bridges.
# Metric: precision = |admitted ∩ is_bridge| / |admitted| ;
#         recall    = |admitted ∩ is_bridge| / |is_bridge across corpus| (all present bridges
#         are admitted here, so recall probes misses; precision is the headline number).
